      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: classify provider code-only failover errors",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nStructured assistant errors that only carry an error `code` (no HTTP status, no body message) were falling through to `null` in the failover reason classifier, preventing model failover from working. Provider-native codes like OpenAI `SERVER_ERROR`, Google `DEADLINE_EXCEEDED`, and Anthropic `API_ERROR` were not recognized.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nProvider-specific code-to-reason mappings now live in each provider's `classifyFailoverReason` hook (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google-family), keeping the core `classifyFailoverReasonFromCode` generic. This prevents provider policy from becoming shared core policy that drifts as providers evolve.\n\n## User Impact\nCode-only provider errors correctly trigger model failover. When the primary provider returns `SERVER_ERROR` (OpenAI), `DEADLINE_EXCEEDED` (Google), or `API_ERROR` (Anthropic), the failover classifier recognizes them and attempts a fallback model.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Tests:**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/failover-error.test.ts --run\n Test Files  1 passed (1) / Tests  91 passed (91)\n\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-helpers/errors-provider-structured-signals.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-helpers/provider-error-patterns.test.ts --run\n Test Files  2 passed (2) / Tests  44 passed (44)\n\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/provider-runtime.test.ts --run\n Test Files  1 passed (1) / Tests  61 passed (61)\n```",
        "branch": "fix-provider-code-failover-reasons",
